38940.title: Banana
38940.extract: The banana is an edible fruit – botanically a berry – produced by several kinds of large herbaceous flowering plants in the genus Musa.

38945.title: Cooking banana
38945.extract: Cooking bananas are banana cultivars in the genus Musa whose fruits are generally used in cooking.

352275.title: Banana Yoshimoto
352275.extract: Banana Yoshimoto (吉本 ばなな, Yoshimoto Banana) (born 24 July 1964) is the pen name of Japanese writer Mahoko Yoshimoto (吉本 真秀子, Yoshimoto Mahoko).

1167404.title: Banana bread
1167404.extract: Banana bread is a type of bread made from mashed bananas.

2823401.title: Cavendish banana
2823401.extract: A Cavendish banana is the fruit of a banana cultivar belonging to the Cavendish subgroup of the AAA cultivar group.

4009568.title: Banana massacre
4009568.extract: The Banana massacre (Spanish: Matanza de las bananeras or Spanish: Masacre de las bananeras) was a massacre of workers for the United Fruit Company that occurred between December 5 and 6, 1928 in the town of Ciénaga near Santa Marta, Colombia.

7183276.title: Blue Banana
7183276.extract: The Blue Banana (French: banane bleue, also known as the European Megalopolis or the Manchester–Milan Axis) is a discontinuous corridor of urbanisation spreading over Western and Central Europe, with a population of around 111 million.

13261606.title: Red banana
13261606.extract: Red bananas are a group of varieties of banana with reddish-purple skin.

42400900.title: Banana Pi
42400900.extract: The Banana Pi is a series of credit card-sized single-board computers based on a low-cost concept for inner software and hardware development and school software learning such as Scratch.
